      <section id="id19583372">
        <title>ACTIVITY: To recognise the place values of digits [LO. 1.4.1]</title>
        <para id="id20183782">1. If we know what the place value of a digit is, it is childâ€™s play to determine the value of that digit. Look at the following numbers. Write down the values of the digits in bold print:</para>
        <para id="id21484383">e.g. : 456 9<emphasis effect="bold">8</emphasis>1  80</para>
        <para id="id19585916">1.1 3 <emphasis effect="bold">2</emphasis>16 417  </para>
        <para id="id20853024">1.2 <emphasis effect="bold">5</emphasis> 641 218  </para>
        <para id="id20307476">1.3 4 1<emphasis effect="bold">8</emphasis>6 046  </para>
        <para id="id21066103">1.4 <emphasis effect="bold">2</emphasis>3 521 000  </para>
        <section id="id20303605">
          <title>DID YOU KNOW?</title>
          <para id="id21193480">If you started to count in seconds, it would take you almost 12 days to count to a million!</para>
